**
- Normally, when using hilt, we just annotate with @hiltApp.
- Usually, this is not suitable for our test case.
- This means that we have to create our own application class.
- This is not done by default but we use the Junit runner that uses hilt test.
application instead of our own.
- This test class should be declared in the defaultConfig as well.

- We then define our test app module.
*

// Testing the fragment with dagger hilt.
- For this we uses the fragment scenarios.